{
  "page": "Lion",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">For the garrison of the City Watch of King's Landing at the Lion Gate, see <a href=\"/index.php/Lions\" title=\"Lions\">Lions</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Lannister.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/d/d5/House_Lannister.svg/300px-House_Lannister.svg.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"330\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/d/d5/House_Lannister.svg/450px-House_Lannister.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/d/d5/House_Lannister.svg/600px-House_Lannister.svg.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:House_Lannister.svg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/index.php/Sigil\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sigil\">sigil</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">House Lannister</a> depicts a golden lion.</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>lion</b> is an animal, similar to real-life <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lion\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Lion\">lions</a>, known to inhabit both <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>. A <i><a href=\"/index.php/Hrakkar\" title=\"Hrakkar\">hrakkar</a></i> is a great white lion found in the <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki_sea\" title=\"Dothraki sea\">Dothraki sea</a> of Essos.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westerosi</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Sigil\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sigil\">sigils</a> depicting lions or lion heads include those of Houses <a href=\"/index.php/House_Casterly\" title=\"House Casterly\">Casterly</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Grandison\" title=\"House Grandison\">Grandison</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Jast\" title=\"House Jast\">Jast</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Lannister\" title=\"House Lannister\">Lannister</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Osgrey\" title=\"House Osgrey\">Osgrey</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Parren\" title=\"House Parren\">Parren</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Polander\" title=\"House Polander\">Polander</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Reyne\" title=\"House Reyne\">Reyne</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_Vikary\" title=\"House Vikary\">Vikary</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Wydman\" title=\"House Wydman\">Wydman</a>.\n</p><p>Because of the Lannisters' sigil, men of the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a> can be called lions.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Lion_Gate\" title=\"Lion Gate\">Lion Gate</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> opens to the <a href=\"/index.php/Goldroad\" title=\"Goldroad\">Goldroad</a>, which leads to the westerlands.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The garrison of the <a href=\"/index.php/City_Watch_of_King%27s_Landing\" title=\"City Watch of King&#39;s Landing\">City Watch of King's Landing</a> stationed at the Lion Gate is called the \"<a href=\"/index.php/Lions\" title=\"Lions\">Lions</a>\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> At sunset, <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a> is believed to resemble a lion in repose.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf762_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf762-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Lion_of_Night\" title=\"Lion of Night\">Lion of Night</a> is a <a href=\"/index.php/Deity\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Deity\">deity</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Yi_Ti\" title=\"Yi Ti\">Yi Ti</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf841_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf841-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> also worshipped in other parts of <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a>, including <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> and <a href=\"/index.php/Asshai\" title=\"Asshai\">Asshai</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf844_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf844-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> In the <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_Black_and_White\" title=\"House of Black and White\">House of Black and White</a> in Braavos, there is an <a href=\"/index.php/Ebony\" title=\"Ebony\">ebony</a> statue of the Lion of Night, depicted as a man with a lion's head seated on a throne.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Pentos\" title=\"Prince of Pentos\">Prince of Pentos</a> keeps a pride of lions in his menagerie.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Unknowclegane.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/08/Unknowclegane.jpg/350px-Unknowclegane.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"306\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/08/Unknowclegane.jpg/525px-Unknowclegane.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/08/Unknowclegane.jpg/700px-Unknowclegane.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Unknowclegane.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Clegane_(founder)\" title=\"Clegane (founder)\">The kennelmaster</a>, founder of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Clegane\" title=\"House Clegane\">House Clegane</a>, saves Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos Lannister</a> from the lioness. Art by tumcolho ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Wood_dancer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wood dancer\">wood dancers</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Children_of_the_forest\" title=\"Children of the forest\">children of the forest</a> are said to have called upon cave lions to fight on their behalf.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf22.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf22.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Lions inhabited the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">western hills</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>. In antiquity, lions made dens in <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a> itself.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf76.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf76.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rssm1379.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rssm1379.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup> According to legend, the founder of House Casterly was the huntsman <a href=\"/index.php/Corlos\" title=\"Corlos\">Corlos</a>, son of <a href=\"/index.php/Caster\" title=\"Caster\">Caster</a>, who lived in a village near where <a href=\"/index.php/Lannisport\" title=\"Lannisport\">Lannisport</a> eventually sprang up. When a lion began preying upon the village's sheep, Corlos tracked him back to his den, a cave in the base of the <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">nearby mountain</a>. Armed only with a spear, Corlos slew the lion and his mate, but spared her newborn cubs. This act of mercy pleased the <a href=\"/index.php/Old_gods\" title=\"Old gods\">old gods</a>, who took favor on Corlos and sent a shaft of sunlight deep into the cave, which shone upon a huge vein of <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf76.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf76.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Later, lions were owned by the <a href=\"/index.php/Kings_of_the_Rock\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kings of the Rock\">Kings of the Rock</a>. According to a semi-canon source, some of King <a href=\"/index.php/Loreon_I_Lannister\" title=\"Loreon I Lannister\">Loreon I Lannister</a>'s lions broke free and slew three of his sons, some say as a curse from <a href=\"/index.php/Morgon_Banefort\" title=\"Morgon Banefort\">Morgon Banefort</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-17\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Sandoq_the_Shadow\" title=\"Sandoq the Shadow\">Sandoq the Shadow</a> is said to have slain lions, <a href=\"/index.php/Bear\" title=\"Bear\">bears</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Wolves\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Wolves\">wolves</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Wyvern\" title=\"Wyvern\">wyverns</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Fighting_pits_of_Meereen\" title=\"Fighting pits of Meereen\">fighting pits of Meereen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Wild lions were seen during the reign of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tytos_Lannister\" title=\"Tytos Lannister\">Tytos Lannister</a>, as the first <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Clegane\" title=\"House Clegane\">House Clegane</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Clegane_(founder)\" title=\"Clegane (founder)\">the kennelmaster</a> at the Rock, saved Tytos from a lioness and lost a leg and three <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">dogs</a> in the effort.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup> Several caged lions were kept in the bowels of Casterly Rock during the childhood of <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a>, a legacy of their grandfather Tytos's time.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_20-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-20\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Khal <a href=\"/index.php/Drogo\" title=\"Drogo\">Drogo</a> hunts and slays a <i><a href=\"/index.php/Hrakkar\" title=\"Hrakkar\">hrakkar</a></i> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki_sea\" title=\"Dothraki sea\">Dothraki sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_21-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot54.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-21\">&#91;21&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Pojypojy_LionPelt.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Pojypojy_LionPelt.jpg/300px-Pojypojy_LionPelt.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"309\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b4/Pojypojy_LionPelt.jpg/450px-Pojypojy_LionPelt.jpg 1.5x, /images/b/b4/Pojypojy_LionPelt.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Pojypojy_LionPelt.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> wearing her <i><a href=\"/index.php/Hrakkar\" title=\"Hrakkar\">hrakkar</a></i> pelt, by Pojypojy ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Handmaid\" title=\"Handmaid\">handmaids</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> make her a cloak from the <i>hrakkar'</i>s pelt, to cover her bald head.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_22-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok12.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-22\">&#91;22&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Within the <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Undying\" title=\"House of the Undying\">House of the Undying</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Qarth\" title=\"Qarth\">Qarth</a>, Daenerys has a series of <a href=\"/index.php/Vision\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vision\">visions</a>, one of which features a white lion.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_23-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok48.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-23\">&#91;23&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentos</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> refers to himself as a lion, which amuses Illyrio Mopatis. He offers to take Tyrion to the <a href=\"/index.php/Prince_of_Pentos\" title=\"Prince of Pentos\">Prince of Pentos</a>'s menagerie so that he can share a cage with a pride of real lions, but Tyrion demurs.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/300_AC\" title=\"300 AC\">300&#160;AC</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Leaf\" title=\"Leaf\">Leaf</a>, one of the <a href=\"/index.php/Children_of_the_forest\" title=\"Children of the forest\">children of the forest</a>, tells <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a> that the great lions of the western hills have all been slain.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_24-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-24\">&#91;24&#93;</a></sup> According to a semi-canon source, a few lions survive in the outlying hills of the <a href=\"/index.php/Westerlands\" title=\"Westerlands\">westerlands</a>, but they mostly have been hunted to extinction.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rssm1379.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rssm1379.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Cersei_Lannister\" title=\"Cersei Lannister\">Cersei Lannister</a> remembers the restless caged lions of her youth, kept in the bowels of <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>, and how she worked up the courage to touch one, while her brother <a href=\"/index.php/Jaime_Lannister\" title=\"Jaime Lannister\">Jaime</a> pulled her away.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_20-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-20\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Lion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/Not_A_Blog\" title=\"Not A Blog\">Not A Blog</a>: <i><a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://georgerrmartin.com/notablog/2022/12/23/a-couple-of-rocks/\">A Couple of Rocks</a></i> (December 23, 2022)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_1\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 1\">Chapter 1</a>, Jaime I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfab16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfab16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - Rhaenyra Triumphant.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfab20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfab20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - The Hooded Hand.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a 